  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Anne Warren Weston begins the letter with family news. Anne has written an article for the Liberator in order to correct a &quot;great mistake in Whittier&apos;s reasoning.&quot; In the last issue of the Recorder, there is a scandalous account of the manner in which the anti-slavery memorial was received by the first ecclesiastical body.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter is written on the verso and margins of the leaflet, the &quot;Address of the Boston Female Anti-Slavery Society to the Women of New England,&quot; and includes their petition to the House of Representatives and Senate to abolish slavery.</subfield>
  </datafield>
